{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17631808","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17631808"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:33:22+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:33:22+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17396"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17396","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17396"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.79,0.02,0.06,0.04,0.09]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10086"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74021"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10086","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10086"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17396"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59497"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"6691"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23605"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23611"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74021","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74021"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe inferior mesenteric artery is one of the branches of the abdominal aorta that supplies the gastrointestinal tract.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the region of supply of the inferior mesenteric artery?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Distal transverse colon to upper rectum","Stomach to duodenum","Jejunum to transverse colon","Caecum to splenic flexure","Lower rectum to anal canal"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Edistal transverse colon to upper rectum\u003C/strong\u003E correctly describes the distribution of the inferior mesenteric artery. This vessel originates from the anterior surface of the abdominal aorta at the level of L3 vertebra and supplies the distal third of the transverse colon, descending colon, sigmoid colon, and upper rectum.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStomach to duodenum\u003C/strong\u003E - This region is supplied by the coeliac trunk\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EJejunum to transverse colon\u003C/strong\u003E - This region is supplied by the superior mesenteric artery\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECaecum to splenic flexure\u003C/strong\u003E - This region is supplied by the superior mesenteric artery\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELower rectum to anal canal\u003C/strong\u003E - This region is supplied by the internal iliac arteries via the middle and inferior rectal arteries\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe main branches of the inferior mesenteric artery are the left colic artery, sigmoid arteries, and superior rectal artery. These vessels form important anastomoses with adjacent arterial territories.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe splenic flexure receives dual blood supply from both the superior mesenteric artery and inferior mesenteric artery via the left colic artery.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The inferior mesenteric artery supplies the distal third of the transverse colon, descending colon, sigmoid colon, and upper rectum.","The inferior mesenteric artery arises from the anterior surface of the abdominal aorta at the level of vertebra L3.","The main branches of the inferior mesenteric artery are the left colic, sigmoid, and superior rectal arteries.","The splenic flexure receives dual blood supply from both the superior mesenteric artery and inferior mesenteric artery via the left colic artery."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59497"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17396"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59497","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59497"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-24T09:06:32+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-24T09:07:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10086"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74021"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4926","links":{"self":"https://app.eme